  <prompt>
    Fill in the AiCompletionNodeExecutor.ExecuteAsync() body up to the LLM call. Read Action's SystemPrompt,
    OutputSchema, and Temperature from NodeExecutionContext. Apply node-level Role/Task/Constraints/Output Fields
    overrides via the existing PromptSchemaOverrideMerger. Resolve template variables from scope (existing
    template-substitution mechanism, mirror AiAnalysisNodeExecutor). The actual IOpenAiClient call happens
    in task 004 — this task prepares the merged inputs and asserts they are correct.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET backend developer extending the AiCompletionNodeExecutor scaffold. Reuse PromptSchemaOverrideMerger
    exactly as AiAnalysisNodeExecutor does — do NOT introduce new merge semantics. Mirror the existing template-
    substitution code path; do NOT clone it.
  </role>

  <goal>
    AiCompletionNodeExecutor.ExecuteAsync() partially implemented up to (but not including) the LLM call:
    1. Reads Action.SystemPrompt + Action.OutputSchema + Action.Temperature from context
    2. Applies node-level overrides via PromptSchemaOverrideMerger (preserves per-node Role/Task/Constraints/Output Fields personalization per Q2 KEEP)
    3. Resolves template variables ({{var}} placeholders) from previous node outputs in scope
    4. Produces a fully-merged (SystemPrompt, OutputSchema, Temperature) tuple ready for the next-task LLM call
    5. Returns NodeOutput.Error if Action is missing (will be hardened by task 005 Validate())
    6. Compiles clean; existing test suite (pre-W1) still green
  </goal>

